<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-01-10T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-01-10T20:00:00-05:00" n="425" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d425">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf. 723.2515/2:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Commission to Negotiate
                                    Peace</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                                </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-01-11T01:00:00+00:00">January 11, 1919—1 a.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>237. [From <persName corresp="#p_LR1">Lansing</persName>.] Your 23
                            December 13, 5 p.m. The President doubts the wisdom of a Bolivian
                            deputation either to the United States or to Paris at the present
                            juncture. <persName corresp="#p_LR1">Lansing</persName>.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Am</hi>[<hi rend="smallcaps">erican</hi>] <hi rend="smallcaps">Mission</hi>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>